            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>Maj. Robert Anderson was the officer in command of the forts in Charleston Harbor when South Carolina began to threaten secession. These personal letters were written on Jan. 2 and Mar. 20, 1861, from Fort Sumter, and reveal Anderson&#039;s apprehensions about the imminent conflict.</p>
                                 <p>The letters are copies of originals in the Robert Anderson Papers in the Library of Congress.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


